      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "\"All sorts of suits would be\nbrought against labor unions. Suits\nfor real grievances and imaginary\nones. A judgment rendered against\na corporation and remaining unpaid\nwould call for receiver or a petition\nin bankruptcy.\n\n\n'In this way employers could easily\ndestroy labor organizations. The\ntrick is at once apparent\"\n\n\nE. S. Potts of the trades council,\nbelieves that an attempt to promote\nthe movement in Spokane will be dis\ncountenanced."
